dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Barnard Castle, drift, sheet 32
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 32 drift. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 54.650000. South Decimal Degree 54.4833. East Decimal Degree -1.5833. West Decimal Degree -2.0333. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights. Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Published on the one-inch scale as Old Series sheet 103 SW in 1881(solid) and 1883 (drift). Resurveyed on the six-inch scale in 1958-1963 by D.A.C. Mills, J.H. Hull, C.R. Burch, and E.A. Francis.".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1969.
